questions.explanation:
## Why This Is Asked
Tests DP understanding with obstacles and modular arithmetic; ensures edge-case handling and ability to implement both bottom-up and top-down approaches.

## Key Concepts
- DP with blockers (Fibonacci variant)
- Bottom-up vs top-down memoization
- Space optimization (O(1) possible with two variables)
- Modulo handling with BigInt or large integers

## Edge Cases
- **Start blocked (step 0)**: Return 0 immediately — no valid paths exist
- **End blocked (step N)**: dp[N] remains 0 since we cannot land on N
- **Consecutive blocked steps**: Creates a barrier; all steps after a chain of 2+ blocked steps will have dp[i]=0 (cannot be reached)

## Code Example
```javascript
const MOD = 1000000007n;

// Bottom-up DP: O(N) time, O(N) space
function countWaysBottomUp(blocked, n) {
  if (blocked[0]) return 0; // start blocked

  const dp = new Array(n + 1).fill(0n);
  dp[0] = 1n;

  for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    if (blocked[i]) {
      dp[i] = 0n; // blocked step: no ways to land here
      continue;
    }
    dp[i] = (dp[i-1] + (i >= 2 ? dp[i-2] : 0n)) % MOD;
  }
  return Number(dp[n]);
}

// Top-down memoization: O(N) time, O(N) space
function countWaysTopDown(blocked, n) {
  if (blocked[0]) return 0; // start blocked

  const memo = new Array(n + 1).fill(-1n);

  function solve(i) {
    if (i < 0) return 0n;    if (i === 0) return 1n;
    if (blocked[i]) return 0n; // this step is blocked
    if (memo[i] !== -1n) return memo[i];

    memo[i] = (solve(i-1) + solve(i-2)) % MOD;
    return memo[i];
  }

  return Number(solve(n));
}

// Space-optimized: O(N) time, O(1) space
function countWaysOptimized(blocked, n) {
  if (blocked[0]) return 0;

  let prev2 = 1n, prev1 = blocked[1] ? 0n : 1n;

  for (let i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
    const curr = blocked[i] ? 0n : (prev1 + prev2) % MOD;
    prev2 = prev1;
    prev1 = curr;
  }

  return Number(n === 0 ? prev2 : prev1);
}
```

## Complexity Analysis
- **Time**: O(N) for all variants — each step computed once
- **Space**: O(N) for basic DP/memoization, O(1) for optimized version
- **Modulo**: Applied at each addition to prevent overflow

