## Why This Is Asked

Tests DP design for constrained substring deletions, palindrome preprocessing, and reconstruction of selections. Combines memoized and tabulated forms, plus memory/time tradeoffs on a practical string problem.

## Key Concepts

- Palindrome preprocessing (center expansion / DP)
- DP over prefixes with up to k deletions
- Reconstructing solution under tie scenarios

## Code Example

```javascript
function maxReward(s, k){
  const n = s.length;
  const P = Array.from({length:n}, ()=>Array(n).fill(false));
  for(let i=0;i<n;i++){ P[i][i]=true; for(let j=i+1;j<n;j++){ /* fill later */ } }
  // assume proper palindrome fill here
  const dp = Array.from({length:n+1}, ()=>Array(k+1).fill(-Infinity));
  for(let t=0;t<=k;t++) dp[0][t]=0;
  // compute bottom-up as described
  return dp[n][0];
}
```

## Why This Is Asked
Tests DP over partitioned sequences with a non-additive batch cost and compares memoization vs tabulation. It also probes edge-case reasoning when K bounds vary.

## Key Concepts
- DP over contiguous partitions
- Range max tracking
- Memoization vs bottom-up trade-offs

## Code Example
```javascript
function minCostPartition(a, K){
  const N=a.length, INF=1e18;
  const Kcap=Math.min(K,N);
  const dp=Array.from({length:N+1}, ()=>Array(Kcap+1).fill(INF));
  dp[0][0]=0;
  for(let i=1;i<=N;i++){
    for(let k=1;k<=Math.min(i,Kcap);k++){
      let maxV=0;
      for(let j=i-1;j>=0;j--){
        maxV = Math.max(maxV, a[j]);
        dp[i][k] = Math.min(dp[i][k], dp[j][k-1] + maxV);
      }
    }
  }
  return dp[N][Kcap];
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- Can you push to O(NK) with a monotone optimization?
- How would you adapt if batch cost were sum of maxes with a penalty per batch?

## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design both memoized and tabulated DP for a non-trivial partition constraint, reinforcing DP patterns and edge-case handling.

## Key Concepts
- Top-down memoization with arrays
- Bottom-up tabulation
- Prefix sums for O(1) range sums
- Power-of-two check with bit trick

## Code Example
```javascript
function countPartitions(nums){
  const n = nums.length;
  const pref = new Array(n+1).fill(0);
  for(let i=0;i<n;i++) pref[i+1]=pref[i]+nums[i];
  const isPow2 = (x)=> x>0 && (x&(x-1))===0;
  // Memoized top-down
  const memo = new Array(n+1).fill(-1);
  const top = (i)=>{
    if(i===n) return 1;
    if(memo[i]!==-1) return memo[i];
    let res = 0;
    for(let j=i+1;j<=n;j++){
      const s = pref[j]-pref[i];
      if(isPow2(s)) res += top(j);
    }
    memo[i]=res; return res;
  };
  // Bottom-up
  const dp = new Array(n+1).fill(0);
  dp[n]=1;
  for(let i=n-1;i>=0;i--){
    let sumWays=0;
    for(let j=i+1;j<=n;j++){
      const s = pref[j]-pref[i];
      if(isPow2(s)) sumWays += dp[j];
    }
    dp[i]=sumWays;
  }
  return {topWays: top(0), bottomWays: dp[0]};
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you optimize for large n or multiple queries on the same array?
- How would you handle large counts and modulo arithmetic to prevent overflow?

