## Time and Memory Trade-offs
- **Time Complexity**: addWord runs in O(L × log K) where L is word length, as we traverse the path and perform heap operations. getTopK runs in O(K × log K) for heap extraction plus O(K log K) for sorting.
- **Space Complexity**: O(N × L + N × K) where N is the total number of unique words—the Trie itself costs O(N × L), and each node stores up to K heap entries.
- **Trade-off**: Increasing K improves result quality but increases memory usage and slows updates. A smaller K is faster but returns fewer suggestions.

