## Key Concepts
- **Trie structure**: Each node contains 26 children (one per letter) and maintains a pass counter representing how many words pass through that node
- **insert operation**: O(m) time, where m is word length; creates nodes as needed and increments pass at each node visited
- **count_with_prefix operation**: O(k) time, where k is prefix length; traverses to the prefix node and returns its pass counter
- **Handling duplicates**: Pass counters naturally accumulate, so duplicate insertions simply increment the counter without special handling

