## Time Complexity Analysis
- insertPhrase: O(L log n) where L is phrase length, n is phrases per prefix
- updateScore: O(L log n) for BST updates plus O(L) for heap propagation
- deletePhrase: O(L log n) for BST removal and heap cleanup
- queryTopK: O(L + k log k) for traversal plus heap extraction

## Memory Trade-offs
- Trie structure: O(N × L) where N is total phrases, L is average length
- BST per node: O(N) total across all nodes
- Top-k heaps: O(N × k) worst-case, but typically O(N) with pruning

## Edge Cases
- Duplicate phrases: update existing entry instead of inserting
- Score ties: use lexicographic ordering as tiebreaker
- Empty prefix: return global top-k from root node
- Large k: consider segment tree for better range queries

## Comparison with Alternatives
- Hash map + sorting: O(1) insert but O(n log n) prefix queries
- Suffix tree: better substring search but higher memory overhead
- Pure Trie with scores: O(L) queries but O(n) updates for score changes
- Hybrid approach (proposed): balances prefix efficiency with dynamic updates

